shine</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0> at: 1/19/02 2:20:11 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukaaine1492.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaaine1492</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>John Holmes Double</span><br>  Posts: 362<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/18/02 2:24:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1062.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire list clerics please read. (Medious issue)</span><hr size=1>    Not a cleric, but may have something constructive.<br>  You are in control of the list and should make a decision, others will follow it since this is the list. Why just make a decision? Your in control and have an idea on how it would be best to manage. Voteing is nice and can be done, but some choices need faster responce. Make the call.<br>I do not know Medious, but I know he is a kid. His parents may not allow him to stay up on schoolnights. Maybe move him to the next school holiday or give a weekend camp? To make this call you have to look at the goal. Is the goal to be democrtatic or get everyone their epic? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/utroydaedagor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Troy Daedagor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dervish Cutthroat</span><br>  Posts: 176<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/18/02 5:44:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1062.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire list clerics please read. (Medious issue)</span><hr size=1> I think that what gets over looked with Ragefire from time to time is that this list, this cooperation, is not a guarantee for you to get a Rage, it is a Privledge. It gives you the best chance that you will find on any other server to get a Rage if you are not part of a large guild. IF YOU DO YOUR PART!<br><br>Think about it. Med has not posted his alt that is in the lair if there is one, he has not posted what times he will be at school or who to get in contact with. These are basic things that many do, that I did, to ensure that people knew what was going on. This list is a Privledge, not your god given right to do what you want when your time comes up. Abuse the system and it will go by the way side. <br><br>I will refrain from saying what I think should be done with Med, I will however give Cay GR's support in what ever she decides to do.<br><br>Please lets all remember what this list is about. <p>Troy Daedagor <BR> 58 Levels of looking out for Tic Taq <BR><a href="http://www.gloriousrising.com"><img src="http://www.gloriousrising.com/pictures/signatures/troysig.jpg"></a> <BR> Being a Cleric is not all Tickly Bears and Lollipop Dreams</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umuidas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MUIDAS</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Orc Legionairre</span><br>  Posts: 81<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/18/02 6:03:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1062.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire list clerics please read. (Medious issue)</span><hr size=1> Dumb question, I thought that when Rage popped, you had a certain amount of time to kill him, or he becomes FFA.  Is this impression incorrect? <p>Muidas<BR>Rogue<BR>Pockets Picked, Backs Stabbed, <BR>Corpses Recovered (Mainly MINE)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/utroydaedagor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Troy Daedagor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dervish Cutthroat</span><br>  Posts: 177<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/18/02 6:55:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1062.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire list clerics please read. (Medious issue)</span><hr size=1> You do have some time provided people know when you will be on. The problem comes when no one is told anything. X Cleric is just no where to be found, no contact, no info, no idea when they will return.<br><br>For instance if Med posted. &quot;Off to school, rage not up at 8am Central. I will be home at 4pm Central to check again.&quot; There is no way in the world anyone would take that rage. However if at 5pm Central he was still not online and working on it he would probably lose it. <p>Troy Daedagor <BR> 58 Levels of looking out for Tic Taq <BR><a href="http://www.gloriousrising.com"><img src="http://www.gloriousrising.com/pictures/signatures/troysig.jpg"></a> <BR> Being a Cleric is not all Tickly Bears and Lollipop Dreams</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ulitli.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Litli</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Werewolf</span><br>  Posts: 325<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/18/02 6:57:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1062.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire list clerics please read. (Medious issue)</span><hr size=1> yes <p>Youngsu 60 Monk<br>Litli 55 Wizard<br>Leader<br>Veil of Shadows<br>litli@veilofshadows.org<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=50939" </a><strong>Magelo Profile</strong></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usolum.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Solum</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/18/02 11:03:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1062.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lazysmile.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire list clerics please read. (Medious issue)</span><hr size=1> YES. not only has he had major problems in the past, which was what all the flames were about. Later on he was not on for rage. He has not posted anything on how to get a hold of him. He has not been on in the past couple of days when i have done a who. And most of all, the whole time we were all talking about this he has yet to make comment, defend himself, or anything else. <p><img border="0" src="http://scionevet.homestead.com/files/ducksig2.gif"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uumpahloompah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Umpah Loompah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/18/02 12:34:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1062.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> boot</span><hr size=1> <br>I'll have to agree with my fellow cleric Solum on this one.  I don't know Medious, but it's clear to me that he isn't making RageFire a priority.  If it means so little to him that he can't bother to be at the camp himself or arrange to have a friend at the camp, toss him out.<br><br>I was clearing HG's last night and was going to assist with buffs for Naggy if necessary as it turns out, the patch was client-side only).  Where was Medious?  No where to be found. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucayleustarshine.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cayleu Starshine</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ragefire is my pet</span><br>  Posts: 351<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/18/02 1:08:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1062.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: boot</span><hr size=1> Since no one's speaking up for Medious here yet, except for the clerics I've polled online so far, here's my reasoning. (Been getting a pretty one-sided responce to give him another chance among those I've talked to online so far)<br><br>Medious is basically guilty of not communicating with us enough, if he would have told us what was going on, we wouldnt have a problem. The incident itself is not a big deal. He was led to believe a patch was coming soon to respawn Naggy, and he went to sleep without telling someone. Soon after, Rage spawned, and 3 hours after that, was taken down. Medious logged on a few hours later the next morning at 6am and would have had him anyway.<br><br>Medious has been camping Ragefire most of the time, by getting support to clear FG's, sitting in the lair, and logging on the cleric briefly once every half hour or so to check the spawn. (which is why he often wasnt found in /who lists) It would have been nice to know this, though. If we had a pattern of neglect, that would be one thing, but punishing him for one mistake seems a bit harsh. <p>Cayleu Starshine<br><font color = blue>Healer of Tunare</font><br><font color=red>Insidious Blood</font></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucayleustarshine.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cayleu Starshine</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0> at: 1/18/02 1:10:36 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucayleustarshine.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cayleu Starshine</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ragefire is my pet</span><br>  Posts: 352<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/19/02 2:21:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1062.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire list clerics please read. (Medious issue)</span><hr size=1> Well, at this point, I knew I said this would last till sunday, but this vote's ended sooner than I thought. With our current totals, it is now mathematically impossible for a two-thirds majority to happen, so as of now, Medious is #2 on the Ragefire list. <p>Cayleu Starshine<br><font color = blue>Healer of Tunare</font><br><font color=red>Insidious Blood</font></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showMessage?topicID=1063.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showMessage?topicID=1060.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1062.topic&index=9><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/add